01/10/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Leaders of the major trade unions agreed on Thursday (September 30th) to hold a joint protest against the government's austerity measures. 
This means that a rally planned for October 7th could be postponed as the various unions scramble to mobilise members. 
The leaders plan to meet again on Monday to discuss the joint strategy. 
Cartel Alfa President Bogdan Hossu said demands concern minimum wage, new jobs, the pension law and the public sector wage law. 
Unions are hoping to mobilise up to 80,000 people. 
(Mediafax, Realitatea, Agerpres, Cotidianul - 30/09/10)
